text.tspan: The 3-day rolling average of the daily number of tests for COVID-19 per thousand people of the country's
population. Given in terms of the number of days since the total confirmed cases reached 1 per million.
Days since the total confirmed cases reached 1 per million people
Source: Official data collated by Our World in Data, European CDC – Situation Update Worldwide
Note: For testing figures, there are substantial differences across countries in terms of the units, whether or not all labs are included, the extent
to which negative and pending tests are included and other aspects. Details for each country can be found at the linked page.
